2 PAIR:{nl}
Two pairs of cards with{nl}
matching values.{waitkey}{clearbox}3 OF A KIND:{nl}
Three cards with the{nl}
same value.{waitkey}{clearbox}STRAIGHT:{nl}
All 5 cards form a{nl}
consecutive sequence.{waitkey}{clearbox}FLUSH:{nl}
All 5 cards share{nl}
the same suit.{waitkey}{clearbox}FULL HOUSE:{nl}
3 OF A KIND combined with{nl}
a remaining pair.{waitkey}{clearbox}4 OF A KIND:{nl}
Four cards with the{nl}
same value.{waitkey}{clearbox}STRAIGHT FLUSH:{nl}
A STRAIGHT where all cards{nl}
share the same suit.{waitkey}{clearbox}5 OF A KIND:{nl}
4 OF A KIND where the{nl}
remaining card is a JOKER.{waitkey}{clearbox}ROYAL FLUSH:{nl}
A STRAIGHT FLUSH formed{nl}
by 10, J, Q, K, and A.{waitkey}{clearbox}              [Hand Notes]              {waitkey}{clearbox}- In this poker game,{nl}
  1 PAIR alone does not{nl}
  count as a hand.{waitkey}{clearbox}- For STRAIGHT-type hands,{nl}
  sequences wrapping from A{nl}
  to 2 are not allowed.{waitkey}{clearbox}- The JOKER is a wild card{nl}
  and can substitute for{nl}
  any hand except 5 OF A KIND.{waitkey}{ret}

