This is a blackjack game{nl}
played 1-on-1 with{nl}
the dealer.{waitkey}{clearbox}The computer acts{nl}
as the dealer.{waitkey}{clearbox}At the start, 2 cards are{nl}
dealt to both the player{nl}
and the dealer.{waitkey}{clearbox}One of the dealer's two{nl}
cards is face down.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: if the dealer's face-up{nl}
card is an Ace, you may{nl}
take INSURANCE.{waitkey}{clearbox}INSURANCE will be explained{nl}
near the end of the{nl}
rules.{waitkey}{clearbox}The player first looks at{nl}
the dealer's card and their{nl}
own, then decides to draw.{waitkey}{clearbox}To draw another card,{nl}
choose "HIT". To stop,{nl}
choose "STAND".{waitkey}{clearbox}As long as your total does{nl}
not exceed 21, you may{nl}
draw up to 7 cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note that STAND is automatic{nl}
in the following cases:{waitkey}{clearbox}- Your first 2 cards form{nl}
  a Blackjack.{waitkey}{clearbox}- Your total reaches 21{nl}
  after the 3rd card or more.{waitkey}{clearbox}- You have drawn 7 cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}- Your total exceeds 21{nl}
  (BUST).{waitkey}{clearbox}Card values: 2-10 count{nl}
as face value.{waitkey}{nl}
J through K count as 10.{waitkey}{nl}
Ace counts as either{nl}
1 or 11.{waitkey}{clearbox}After the player STANDs,{nl}
the dealer draws cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}If the player's total doesn't{nl}
exceed 21 and is higher than{nl}
the dealer's,{waitkey}{nl}
or the dealer BUSTs,{nl}
the player wins.{waitkey}{clearbox}If both totals are equal,{nl}
or both have Blackjack,{nl}
it is a draw{waitkey}{nl}
and your betted coins{nl}
are returned.{waitkey}{clearbox}Besides HIT and STAND,{nl}
the player may also use{waitkey}{nl}
"D. DOWN" and{nl}
"SPLIT".{waitkey}{clearbox}   <D. DOWN>   (DOUBLE DOWN)   {waitkey}{clearbox}Can only be used when{nl}
the player has 2 cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}The player agrees to HIT{nl}
exactly one more card, and{nl}
doubles their bet.{waitkey}{clearbox}Cannot be used if you have{nl}
fewer coins than{nl}
your current bet.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you win after DOUBLE DOWN,{nl}
the payout is doubled.{waitkey}{clearbox}   <SPLIT>   {waitkey}{clearbox}Can be used when the first{nl}
2 cards dealt have the{nl}
same value.{waitkey}{clearbox}The 2 cards are separated{nl}
into 2 hands and the{nl}
game continues on both.{waitkey}{clearbox}Cannot be used if you have{nl}
fewer coins than{nl}
your current bet.{waitkey}{clearbox}D. DOWN can still be used{nl}
in each hand after{nl}
a SPLIT.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: after a SPLIT, an Ace{nl}
plus a 10-K combination{nl}
does not count as Blackjack,{waitkey}{nl}
but is counted as 21.{waitkey}{clearbox}{nl}
[About INSURANCE]{waitkey}{clearbox}INSURANCE is a kind of{nl}
bet that is offered only{nl}
when the dealer's first card{waitkey}{nl}
is an Ace.{waitkey}{clearbox}Choose YES to take insurance,{nl}
or NO to decline.{waitkey}{clearbox}Choosing NO proceeds with{nl}
the game as normal.{waitkey}{clearbox}Choosing YES: you first pay{nl}
a premium equal to half{nl}
your bet amount.{waitkey}{nl}
Then, if the dealer's{nl}
hidden card is 10-K,{waitkey}{nl}
meaning a Blackjack,{nl}
your bet is forfeited, but{waitkey}{nl}
3x the premium is returned{nl}
and the game ends.{waitkey}{clearbox}If the dealer's card is{nl}
A through 9,{waitkey}{nl}
the premium is forfeited{nl}
and the game continues{nl}
as normal.{waitkey}{ret}

