Numbers 1-9 are placed{nl}
randomly in a 3x3 grid{nl}
of 9 squares.{waitkey}{clearbox}Figure out the arrangement{nl}
of those numbers.{waitkey}{clearbox}The faster you solve it,{nl}
the better the prize{nl}
you receive.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you can't answer within{nl}
the allowed number of tries,{nl}
it's game over.{waitkey}{clearbox}The allowed tries equals{nl}
the number of "RESULT"{nl}
slots on the right.{waitkey}{clearbox}Each time your answer{nl}
is wrong, it is recorded{nl}
in the RESULT slots.{waitkey}{nl}
Use these as hints for{nl}
your next guess.{waitkey}{clearbox}Also, "CHOOSED" shown{nl}
above the input area{nl}
lights up each selected{waitkey}number when chosen, and{nl}
goes dark when not. Use this{nl}
to check that all numbers{nl}
1-9 are used exactly once.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: this game uses{nl}
"Metal Cards" instead{nl}
of coins.{waitkey}{ret}

